==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guanidine
<hw>Gua"ni*dine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A strongly alkaline base,
<chform>NH2.CNH.NH2</chform>, formed by the oxidation of guanin, and
also obtained combined with methyl in the decomposition of creatin.
Boiled with dilute sulphuric acid, it yields urea and ammonia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guaniferous</ent>⟦br⟧
